The White House is committed to working with Central American countries to address the root causes of migration. They are focused on promoting prosperity and regional economic integration, enhancing security, and promoting improved governance in the region. They are providing trade capacity building assistance, supporting energy and transportation infrastructure projects, and funding technical assistance for clean energy development. They are also working on police reform, community security, and attacking organized crime to enhance security. Additionally, they are helping countries improve revenue collection and public sector fiscal management, strengthen civil society, and reinforce democratic institutions to improve governance. Various U.S. agencies are involved in these efforts to support Central American countries.